      "term": "reticulocytosis",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "C2",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "A condition in which there is an increased number of reticulocytes in the blood, usually as a response to blood loss or anemia.",
          "examples": [
            "Reticulocytosis is often seen after acute hemorrhage as the body replaces lost red blood cells.",[8][5]
            "The laboratory report showed reticulocytosis consistent with hemolytic anemia."[5][8]
          ],
          "collocations": [
            "marked reticulocytosis",
            "compensatory reticulocytosis",
            "reticulocytosis following hemorrhage",
